<review>Found this family owned propane business near my area. With the COVID restrictions this past year and the on and off bans on dinning at restaurants, we‚Äôve been doing more home grilling and camping and consuming more propane.

Recently bought a 5lb tank for camping use and brought it here for the first fill. Had no issues for the fill (1.2 gallon) and Nona was super funny and informative - she explained how to see the manufacture date of tanks and mine was just made a couple of months ago(tanks can only be used for 12 years before they need to be re-certified).

Wessel charges by the gallon for the refills. A 20lb tank will typically have 4.6 gallons capacity. In January of 2021, they charge $3.05 per gallon (plus tax) which is roughly around $14 for a 20lb tank. This is cheaper then other refill places I know of and much cheaper then tank exchanges. For tank exchanges, they normally come with 80% fill.

I would highly recommend this place for your next propane tank refill.</review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN1i7NJFBl5zasACmhm370Z42Lu0QzbDr4KM4MH=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMezC1hm6jWnZsCustDVjQp7SxdcY8Pwibic8lN=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNXQNYlAUd-XjxOehjZW01JKmSah19S2iRjcqj3=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMwOyKGvUESl_s5SV3iMR4SdsxI9igNJqWoq-Lf=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNcz8GfO0KHpXN5Y32SwS7_V2zaAtG9K3u5TBHb=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMe3OPLzZDaknp2bPhltumH5DGti_jHzqpiXjWW=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pictures><response>None<//response><gmapID>0x80c2d7a74fdd3a41:0x900743ef68002719< /gmapID></record>

<review>I come to Wessel everytime I need to refill my propane tanks. I mainly use propane for cooking, BBQ, and outdoor heaters.

Everytime I come here, I always get great service. That's what keeps me coming back.

I live not too far, but if I did live farther away I would probably still go out of my way to come here for my propane needs.

The prices are great. I'm always delighted with how inexpensive it is to fill my tanks. This is a family owned business, and they are great people.

They provide services thats always above and beyond what you get at U-Haul, or any other of these propane place.

I'm probably going to be a life time customer, as long as they are around! If you check them out, if your able to, its always nice to give a tip to whomever helps you.

They don't ask for it, or even impy it or anything like that, but COVID is hurting small businesses right now. I would do anything I can to help these places stay around as long as possible.</review>< pictures>

<Name>Tom Cato</Name>< Date>
1618123558928</Date>
<Rating>5< /Rating>< Text>
I eat a lot of sushi and I happen to run across this restaurant today and because it has a high rating, I decided to try it. Boy, am I glad that we stopped. The food was spectacular. This is the freshest fish that I've had in a long time. Every component of what we ordered was top notch.

I had a Ruby Roll which was so tasty and large. It's basically a big California roll with spicy crab on top. That could have been my whole meal but being the glutton that I am I also ordered another roll. Unfortunately I can't remember the name of it but it too was very tasty.

My daughter ordered the chirashi dinner which included a salad and soup. The miso soup was good and the salad with the ginger dressing was really good. My daughter let me taste the sashimi on her meal and it was so fresh, it melted in your mouth.

This will become my favorite sushi restaurant. You should make it yours too!< /Text>

<Rating>3<//Rating>< text>
We ordered the omakase sashimi platter and spicy edamame with the chicken thigh and pork belly yakitori. The service was extremely friendly and quick, but the sashimi was sadly disappointing. The slices provided lacked flavor. The scallops and fresh octopus were the best items on the plate, but the rest was just... boring. I really wanted to love this place.

The chicken thigh was good, but the sauce was too sweet. The pork belly was over-cooked and very tough to chew.

Honestly, the stars are more for the service than the flavor of food.< /text>

<Text>Takaraya! I think I spelled the name right. Let's take a trip to Japan. Simple food without the fancy decoration and price. I like this place because it's never really that busy. The food quality is okay. I think the sushi is better than the entree items. I tried the Chicken katsu curry The chicken was tender but a bit small for 7 dollars, about the size of my palm. It came with a huge plate of rice and curry on the side, which I liked. The curry was a little different that the Japanese curry I'm use too. It tasted more like Chinese curry that you get from 99 Ranch. The spice tuna was not too bad. The eel could have been better. Overall, it isn't Mitusuwa market quality, but will satisfy your craving for sushi the same way McDonalds will satisfy a burger craving. It's not bad, but it may leave you wanting more. I haven't tried the ramen and hope to try it next time.

Recommended to try. I'm always a fan of sushi without the crowds and the super expensive price tags.</Text>< Pics>

<UserId.>100300478235392619766</UserId.><review>I dont know how I lived in the area for so long and never saw this gem of a spot.

I have family in Sinaloa and often travel to Los Mochis to visit, food is an important part of their culture and their daily lives. Its always fantastic and just the best. I miss it often when I'm not with family and am always in the look out for amazing Mexican food.

When I saw the sign for Sinaloa Fish Market and Restaurant I knew I had to try it.

Walking in, the place clean and has a friendly environment.

We ordered a few small things to try; Fish Taco, Shrimp Taco, Asada Taco and a Shrimp and Octopus Tostada.

They are all on point and fantastic! The salsa was the perfect amount of heat with a great flavor. I cannot wait to come back and try more!!

The place was also pretty empty, I encourage you to try this place out, they are amazing!! Please let's help this local business thrive!!!< /review></record></dataset><record>

< text>
This is one of the most visually stunning churches I've ever been to. From the altar to the statues, everything was thoughtfully chosen. I used to come here in my youth and always loved the friendly community. Now, I only go when I'm back in town visiting my parents. The improvements they've made over the years are impressive. < Text>
I grew up being a parishioner here since I was a child and I love the beautiful church but I am sad to say that the staff on the other hand is not very nice at all. she was rude disrespectful and very picky about everything. I called in for a baptism for my child and Rachel who I spoke over the phone, told me I have to come into the office. After a lengthy process and explanation from Rachel and making sure everything was right Rachel told me she does not handle Vietnamese baptism and to come back during the weekend to turn in my paperwork. i took time off of work to stop by and made sure to be able to see her so she can help me. I return 2 days later and she refused to take in my paperwork and told me I had to talk to the weekend receptionist. She gave me an attitude and went to help someone else and ignored me so I just decided to go to another church. saint columban church need new better staff. I do not think I will ever come back again. It is very disheartening. How can you work at a church and have that attitude...?< /Text>

< text>
We own a C70 Volvo that we bought new from Ontario Volvo in 2010.  Other than a few oil changes and some tires, we have had all our service done at Ontario Volvo.  Recently, our AC stopped blowing cold air and we did not think twice about having Ontario Volvo and their Service team do the evaluation and repairs.  Ivan is very professional and understands the Gold Standard of Service Delivery.  He kept us up to date and informed about our issue.  The repair was done in the time stated and we headed in to pick up our vehicle.  We realized that the air was not blowing cold.  Ivan helped us test it and they quickly evaluated the issue and offered to correct it immediately.  The next day Ivan informed us of the issue and that it was corrected.  They also offered to make it right to our satisfaction.  Thank you Ivan, thank you Volvo of Ontario.  While we do not want to see you soon, we are more than comfortable that you will handle any of our concerns.< /text>

<rate>1< /rate>< review>
It's really sad to see that a dealer has to lie to it's customers in order to stay afloat.

For the last few months, I've noticed a few unusual quirks in my S80. Headlights are dim, and alternator feedback penetrates the cabin quite loudly through the stereo. On top of that, using cabin electronics causes the other electronics to glitch out, some warning lights are on the dash, when the vehicle is shut off the alternator whines loudly, yadda yadda. It's not a huge deal, but it can be an annoyance.

I know it's an alternator, a few friends have experienced the problem before and it turned out to be the alternator, and an independent shop I have visited said it's the alternator.

I needed to get an oil change for my vehicle anyways, so it's time to take it to the dealer to get it taken care of and also get a quote for replacement of the alternator.

First off, I call asking for pricing on their oil changes. The secretary put me on hold and I waited for 10 min. She came back on the line and apologized, telling me it would be very soon. I wait another 10 minutes. Nothing. Tired of waiting, I hang up and just Google the average cost.

Arrive at the dealer for a 10:30 appointment. Wait about 45 minutes (11:15) to actually get the car looked at. So far I'm not impressed.

Asked service man to change oil and perform diagnostic. Time goes by. Car comes back.

"We performed the diagnostic. Results are back"

"Did you change the oil?"

"Oh.... no."

Car goes. Car comes back. Here's the kicker though, report says nothing about the alternator, but instead says almost every other electrical component needs to be replaced at a cost of $1500. I don't know if I should laugh or be disgusted.

There's no question at all, 1000000% sure that the alternator needs to be replaced (even if it's not the root of the experienced electrical problems). The fact that they said it's absolutely perfect tells me without a doubt they are lying.

Look, I'm not stupid. I know that Volvo has had abysmal sales in the US recently. That means dealers are making no money on vehicle sales and as a result, have to catch up by marking up, and probably even lying about service. They want me to spend all my precious money before they actually attack the problem itself in order to maximize their profit. The dealer is only trying to stay afloat, I get that - people have mouths to feed. I still don't think it's right to lie to customers.

Do yourself a favor and see if there's any European specialized maintenance shops in your area. They probably don't have to lie to keep themselves above water.

And who charges $300 for a spare key? Really?<//review>

<username>Dibakar Basu< /username>< time>
1547408195704< /time>
<Rating>4</Rating>< review>
One of my most favourite Indian grocery shop. They have a very small shop run by all family members mostly, good part is unlike Namaste plaza, this is very organized and they have a very good collection of all Indian products be it sweet or spices or oil or any other. They keep small amount but good quality of Indian vegetables and some Indian frozen delicacies too. However their price might seem a little higher occasionally but their deli section is really worthy of money. Specially the sweets are fresh and tasty. It‚Äôs always advisable to call and check if they have a certain thing at their shop and that way you can save a lot of time and gas. Also their deli section remains closed on certain days of the week.

The only bad thing is the parking which is hard to get on busy day and time.</review>

Chee Cake, Chee Cake, Cheecake (a take on Cheeburger, Cheeburger, Cheeburger from a long forgotten SNL classic with John Belushi in the Olympia Cafe...see Wiki), absolutely certain to release tons of Dopamine in your brain & trigger old NYC genuine fresh CHEESECAKE. Before I even get to the food. When you walk in, the furnishing is "Eh". Didn't have half of the stuff on the menu. I wanted the Bone-in chicken breast meal, the guy said "I only have boneless"- that was ok, I like boneless. For my sides I wanted mac & cheese, corn- he replied "I don't have corn. I only have Mac, greens, yams & veggies". They had like 5 flavors of soda on menu, I wanted a pineapple - > "I only have orange & Limon lime". Then I had to wait like 40-45 mins for the food, smh. It was fresh, sure, but couldn't go here on lunch break, takes too long. Some people came in after me and wanted to order wings, I think- they didn't have wings.

Now to the food: chicken was seasoned well and fully cooked. Mac was ok, I've had better, but also have had worse. I don't know if I'll give it another chance, maybe I'll call in the order next time. The prices are reasonable. Black owned & Black run, but got to do better on the presentation of the place.< /Text>

<Name>Robert Binder<//Name><date>1598487626275<//date><Rate>5< /Rate><Review>Had the best experience having lunch/brunch with my family this weekend. We were sat right away by a very welcoming host and taken to a table by the TVs so my grandfather could watch the soccer game. Our server, Jacob, was fantastic! He was extremely attentive, helpful, super funny, and made us all feel like family. The food was excellent all around and our drinks were constantly refilled before getting near the bottom. <Rating>2<//Rating>< Text>
This is my review based on this one experience. I‚Äôve been before without the issues we had this time, but I will likely not return anytime soon.
Had a drink at the bar without any issues while waiting for a table.
The table took longer than quoted, but not by too much and it was a Friday evening, so somewhat expected. I think the process for having guests check back in once notified could be improved, especially when busy. There was no clear spot for us to return, so we waited in line with people adding their names to the list.
Once seated, we were greeted warmly and promptly, but when it came time to order drinks, it was clear the server was not well-versed in the available options. We asked about flavored spirits and the server just named brands, not flavors. When we asked for something listed as as an ingredient in a specialty cocktail, she said they didn‚Äôt have it. When the drink arrived, it wasn‚Äôt made correctly and the replacement took an unusually long time.
Now to the food.  I started with a side salad, which, while it looked appealing, had a pool of water at the bottom and was drenched in gloppy ranch dressing.
The pot pie I ordered was decent and the others at the table enjoyed their entrees, but they weren‚Äôt anything special.
Unfortunately, the food was not good enough to overcome the clunky service to make me want to return.</Text>

<text>This is a gluten free review.

Gluten free menu: Yes! Request a gluten free menu when you are being seated

What I ordered: I did the unconventional and ordered gluten free carrot cake before my meal, followed by a Cobb salad and French fries

Gluten free options: 3/5
Super impressed that they have a gluten free cake. This is not your average gluten free dessert, but it‚Äôs made with almond flour and was absolutely incredible.

Food: 4/5
I was impressed with the cake and the fried. The salad was short on a lot of toppings. It was 90% lettuce and 10% toppings. Felt a little jipped this time around when it came to the salad. The rest of the meal was amazing though, which is why I can justify this rating. They really do have the best French fries. Perfectly crispy!

Service: 2/5
Our server was friendly but not attentive. It took about 15 mins to receive the cake. We also were never asked for a water refill. I also noticed that most of the servers congregate near the bar, are talking, laughing, and then they disperse at around the same time. Not really efficient for taking care of their customers.

Location: 4/5
Parking is abundant and the restaurant is easy to locate

Ambiance: 3/5
Casual and comfortable environment. You can bring your dog to eat on the patio.

Price: 4/5
$37 for two people. Two entrees, appetizer, no drinks. Not bad!

Overall score: 4/5<//text></record>

<rating>4</rating>< review>
Went for lunch with around 15 co-workers. Our waiter did not get upset with this, and got all our orders correctly. I ordered the shrimp tacos and they were amazing. However, one of my co-workers is allergic to shell fish, and they seemed to have mixed her chicken with some of the seafood and she got sick, even after informing the waiter. Another co-worker ordered a pulled pork sandwich and there was hardly any meat. Those that ordered a salad or soup got full with them before their actual meal, so plan accordingly. The decor is fun to look at as a dog lover too. The portions are a good size, and service was good. I would come back.< /review>

Bartender: what can I get you?
Me: do you have pickle juice for a pickle back?
Bartender: no, the kitchen does; but I can't leave the bar just to get it for you.
Me: I'll just take a whiskey neat then.
Me thinking: the bar doesn't have food either, but how does food prepared in the kitchen magically appear at the bar for other patrons? < Text>
I cannot say enough about the staff here. They are absolutely amazing! We have been having a rough 24 hours with our pooch Titus and decided to bring him here after the ER visit to help settle our nerves and get him some food as well. So many friendly people, including staff, were asking about our dog because the recent shavings he received are very noticeable. After we ate and asked for our bill, our waitress (I apologize for not remembering her name, kinda out of it with the sick pooch and all) told us that we were all set and everything was taken care of. This left us puzzled and she told us that the staff came together and they just wanted to take care of us. I cannot ever thank the employees of Lazy Dog enough for such amazing compassion and empathy during our extremely stressful time. They have made us customers for life and we will definitely be back, definitely while we still have Titus with us. Thank you guys for turning a very difficult time into an amazing one!< /Text>

<review>This is a slightly pricier restaurant offering American fare, much along the lines of Cheesecake Factory. However, this restaurant has a cozier, friendlier feel. Maybe it has to do with their policy of allowing dogs to eat with you on the outside patio (none are allowed inside, so you can enjoy your food dog-allergy-free if that applies). In any case, their food options are solid. The pot roast and chicken pot pie come highly recommended. Service is excellent. Parking can be a bit tricky at peak meal times, and there can be a wait as well.</review>< resp>

< Name>
Bee Cee< /Name>
<rate>3</rate><Response>None<//Response>< Text>
Average food with mediocre service.
I've been many times and it's stayed true to form. The atmosphere is really pretty cool its always fun to see the different dogs that are there. However, that really only goes so far. The food has never been "bad", but I've never had excellent either. Seasoning, doneness, temperature, something is always just not quite right. Not enough to complain about, but never where you're excited about what you just got either. As for the service, I don't know if they have too much rotation or just hire the servers that aren't on their A-game, but again it's never quite what you expect. Either they walk by you several times when you're drinks are empty, they don't know the menu, or just seem too busy... Will I go back again? Yeah, I'm sure I will. But it's never at the top of my list, it's more like "well, we could go to Lazy Dog, we haven't been in awhile".<//Text>

<review>This particular restaurant has above average service. When it gets busy the service level on things like refills, clearing your table, getting your check declines. But generally it is good. Servers typically are smiling and friendly and always smiling.

They have a very varied menu. Tons of things to select from and interesting unique items as well. They put unique touches on things such as the quesadilla where they brown the cheese on the outside of the tortilla in addition to the filling.

I think they have some of the best fish and chips around. Nice thick pieces of cod. The cole slaw and fries are great too with this dish. The other item I love is the breaded pork chop.

Their corn wheel seasonal appetizer is great. Like getting Mexican street corn (elotes)

Nice ambiance and you can bring your dog to sit outside and dine on the patio< /review>< Pics>
None< /Pics>

Excellent food (the pot roast is my Favorite!!), Excellent service (our server was Awesome!! ...although I just blanked on his name, so I'll have to get back to you), and all around Excellent vibe and atmosphere! Always look forward to any chance I have to go to Lazy, and I've never been disappointed! Tonight there was 5 of us for dinner and Everyone loved the choices they made. I had the pot roast of course, another had the fettuccine Alfredo with chicken and shrimp, someone else had the Black and Blue pizza, one had the sundried tomato chicken pasta (not sure the real name of it), and one had the hushpuppies. Sooooo  yummy!! ...Oh, and we also shared an order of Brussels sprouts. Mmmmm!! ....Only complaint is that I'm so full now!! :-/< /Review>

< text>
We have a dog and we used to walk here all the time, but we had a number of bad experiences and haven't been back. I think the biggest deterrent is the inconsistency of their drinks. We had some awful margaritas once (I know it's not a Mexican place but margaritas aren't that difficult to make), and their signature cocktails are never the same from one visit to the next. If we're going out for dinner, drinks are an important part of the experience.<//text>

<Name>Nour Eldin El Ahlawee<//Name><date>1458686417752<//date>< Rate>
1< /Rate>
< Review>
I took my wife for a lunch at the restaurant last weekend, this is maybe the 5th. or 6th. time to go there, but it will be the last for sure.  We waited for about 20 minutes to be seated which is fine as they looked quite busy. But we were seated outside as requested but we were seated in the sun. My wife asked the waiter to see if we could be moved to another table that had just become vacant and Seth the waiter was very polite and moved us to the shady table.  He came after a few minutes and said that we might have to move back to the other table because he was told by his manager to send us back as that table was going to be giving to a different party and we may have move back to the table in the sun.  He came back again and told us that we COULD stay as he "fought for us".  I really did not like the idea I called the manager and told him that as a courtesy to the customer they should have kept their seating problem away from the customer I did not have to feel any stress because of their seating situation, he said that he was going to let us stay on the current table in a tune made me feel that he was doing us a favor!! I told him that he was not doing me any favor. And to be honest this may not sound a big deal, but we both felt awkward and were not going to stay if we were told we had to move back.
We are not going back to this location, but we love the location in Orange as well as Brea
Mohamed Anwar<//Review>
